The paper deals with propositional satisfiability (SAT) and its application to propositional disjunctive answer set programming (ASP), which are both topics in artificial intelligence (AI) and logic (LO). The paper also utilizes techniques from parameterized complexity (DS) and combinatorics (DM). Additionally, the paper involves transformations and reductions (CC) from one problem to another. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI and cs.LO, followed by cs.DS, cs.CC, and cs.DM.
